  "title": "feat(router): plug router as a middleware",
  "body": "This PR introduces the concept of middleware in InstantSearch. It's leveraged internally to plug the routing system.\r\n\r\n## Why\r\n\r\nWhen building tools on top of InstantSearch, you had no way to subscribe and detect changes.\r\n\r\nSince Federated Search came in v4, you can build more complex apps, but they're sometimes hard to debug. You can now dynamically add and remove indices, which impacts the UI state and the search parameters sent to Algolia. To help debug apps in this situation, I plan to build a dev tool to **visualize the InstantSearch tree**.\r\n\r\nThis visualizer could be plugged as a Storybook addon (I built a POC based on this PR already) or as a browser extension (think like React Devtools).\r\n\r\nBuilding such integrations was not possible before this middleware system.\r\n\r\n## Middleware definition\r\n\r\nMiddleware can be attached to InstantSearch with the `use` method.\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nfunction router({ instantSearchInstance }) {\r\n  return {\r\n    onStateChange({ state }) {\r\n      // write in the history\r\n    },\r\n    subscribe() {},\r\n    unsubscribe() {},\r\n  };\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction logger({ instantSearchInstance }) {\r\n  return {\r\n    onStateChange({ state }) {\r\n      // log changes\r\n    },\r\n    subscribe() {},\r\n    unsubscribe() {},\r\n  };\r\n}\r\n\r\nconst search = instantsearch({\r\n  /* ... */\r\n});\r\n\r\nsearch.use(router, logger).start();\r\n```\r\n\r\nMiddleware can also be attached after the search starts.",
